    <h2>What's inside the PDF</h2>

    <p>The pack is a single plain-English PDF workbook. It walks you through your claim from start to finish, with the letters and templates you need at each stage. It includes:</p>

    <ol>
      <li><strong>A simple start-here guide</strong> — explains what Section 75 is, how the process works, and what to expect from your bank.</li>
      <li><strong>A 5-minute Section 75 checker</strong> — a short set of questions to confirm your purchase qualifies before you write to your bank.</li>
      <li><strong>A one-page claim details worksheet</strong> — a structured form to pull together the key facts of your case before you start writing.</li>
      <li><strong>An evidence checklist</strong> — tailored to the most common claim types, so you know exactly what to gather and send.</li>
      <li><strong>An initial Section 75 claim letter</strong> — a formal letter to your credit card provider's disputes team, citing Section 75(1) of the Consumer Credit Act 1974. Covers non-delivery, faulty goods, goods not as described, and business failure.</li>
      <li><strong>A short chase message</strong> — a follow-up template for use if your bank does not respond within the required timeframe.</li>
      <li><strong>Rebuttal templates for common bank rejection reasons</strong> — ready-to-send responses covering the most frequent grounds banks use to reject valid claims, including overseas supplier arguments and part-payment disputes.</li>
      <li><strong>A Financial Ombudsman complaint template</strong> — a formal complaint letter for use if the bank issues a final rejection or fails to respond within eight weeks.</li>
      <li><strong>A plain-English glossary and official sources</strong> — definitions of the terms your bank will use, and links to the primary legislation and FOS guidance.</li>
    </ol>

